lns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.eallion.com/1314520/featured.png"/></item><item><title>故事</title><link>https://www.eallion.com/100/</link><pubDate>Sun, 26 Jun 2011 13:42:25 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.eallion.com/100/</guid><description>年少时读过一个知音故事：男孩为求婚在女孩窗前苦等 99 天，却在最后一天缺席。真爱需要坚持，但尊严不容践踏！</description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.eallion.com/100/featured.png"/></item><item><title>为爱而哭</title><link>https://www.eallion.com/cry-for-love/</link><pubDate>Sat, 11 Jun 2011 22:49:30 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.eallion.com/cry-for-love/</guid><description>曾经的坚强在憋屈与无奈中溃散，但微小渴望的满足仍能带来巨大幸福！</description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.eallion.com/cry-for-love/featured.png"/></item><item><title>爱一个人</title><link>https://www.eallion.com/love-someone/</link><pubDate>Tue, 31 May 2011 13:13:18 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.eallion.com/love-someone/</guid><description>爱一个人需要理解与开解，道歉与感恩，改正错误而非仅认错，体贴体谅而非忍受，宽容不纵容，支持不支配，慰问不质问，倾诉不控诉，铭记而非遗忘，真诚交流而非机械交代，默默祝福而非苛求，浪漫但不浪费，慎重牵手更不轻言放手！</description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.eallion.com/love-someone/featured.png"/></item><item><title>我喜欢的人和喜欢我的人</title><link>https://www.eallion.com/mychoose/</link><pubDate>Thu, 10 Mar 2011 08:00:32 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.eallion.com/mychoose/</guid><description>在必须结婚却未遇真爱时，选择自己喜欢的人而非喜欢自己的人更明智。自信能让对方逐渐爱上自己，且不奢求回报反而可能收获惊喜。依赖他人喜欢而任性妄为是危险的，因为感情可能变化。缘分终究是注定的，强求不如顺其自然。</description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.eallion.com/mychoose/featured.png"/></item><item><title>情人节快乐</title><link>https://www.eallion.com/valentines-day/</link><pubDate>Mon, 14 Feb 2011 22:22:40 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.eallion.com/valentines-day/</guid><description>情人节快乐！感谢一路相伴，愿每一天都充满喜悦与幸福。保持微笑，珍惜当下，让温暖常驻心间！</description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.eallion.com/valentines-day/featured.png"/></item></channel></rss>